{
  "texts": [
    "At the time of the study, Twitter's data availability, its widespread use -more than 300 millions of monthly active users worldwide-and its predominant role in political communication justify our choice to use it as our experimental field for testing the proposed framework.",
    "Moreover, as measured empirically, Twitter is also a digital media where negative contents are more viral than others (see Figure 24) and where the users themselves are biased towards the production of negative contents (see Figure 21).",
    "This raises the important question, both for public debate and for the well-being of users, of the extent to which this overflow of negativity is due to Twitter's algorithmic architecture.",
    "Briefly, Twitter is an online social network launched in 2006 allowing its users to exchange publicly 280 characterslong messages that are broadcasted to theirs \"followers\", users who subscribed the author's account.",
    "Content is displayed to the users on a feed called Home timeline according to personalized recommendations."
  ]
}